Former Senator who represented the Kogi West Senatorial District in the 8th National Assembly, Senator Dino Melaye has said that Nigerians are fed up with the All Progressives Congress, APC-led government which he described as a Non-Governmental Organisation, NGO. The former lawmaker stated this on Friday night when he featured on a Channels TV programme, ‘Politics Today’. Dino who is currently a chieftain of the opposition party, PDP, said President Muhammadu Buhari was the greatest scam in Africa. Speaking on the current security crisis ravaging the entire country, the former senator alleged that Nigerian security agencies are, “behaving like a boyscouts all because of corruption and ineptitude.” He said the security agencies fighting the insurgents are not excelling despite their successes in international peacekeeping due to corruption in the government. According to him, Nigeria had not faced,”terrible security and economic situation like this before. “The Buhari agenda is the greatest scam that came out of Africa. Once I was blind, now I can see. How can one remain in a political party and support the presidency with what is happening today in Nigeria? I regret seriously supporting that because we were scammed. “Nigerians are fed up with this NGO called the APC. The insecurity in this country; we have never seen anything like this; I cannot fathom it. Recall that Melaye was a major critic of former president, Goodluck Jonathan during the 2015 presidential election. However, he recently apologized to Goodluck Jonathan, stating that he was blind while supporting the current president, Muhammadu Buhari.